Corrosions on u1900, u7100, u7600, Q7010
minor corrosions on Q7630, u7310, Q7310, Q7320
R5488 - pin2 was burnt. (next to SMC)
keyboard - pin4 - was burnt (PP3V42_G3H)

i have replaced the stuff above already. PP3V42_G3H is little low.


[B]dead SMC[/B], any ideas?

title: 820-4927 - liquid damaged, green, orange light, not turning on.
message:
First check the usual suspects U1950 pin 8, U6100 and termination resistors in the data lines and the traces/vias to U6100/termination resistors. 

Corrosion on U7310 is worrying though, CPU is very easily killed. What is resistance to GND on L7310?

title: 820-4927 - liquid damaged, green, orange light, not turning on.
message:
U1950 pin 8 - 3.411  - corrosion was on pin8, i replaced U1950. made no diffiernces 

resistance to GND on L7310 - 28.7 ohms

i'll checked all resistors on SPI Bus Series Termination. all perfect.

title: 820-4927 - liquid damaged, green, orange light, not turning on.
message:
did a USC, after drying. i was able to perform a smc bypass. i could hear chime, fan spin. vcore was 1.8v.

now it is hard to get into smc bypass, sometime work, most of time doesn't.

i also notice pubs_g3h sometime become 12.23v

title: 820-4927 - liquid damaged, green, orange light, not turning on.
message:
ok, i've just reflowed smc

now it posts without doing a smc bypass,

i'll do more test and might need to change smc...

title: 820-4927 - liquid damaged, green, orange light, not turning on.
message:
Check if voltage on PPBUS_G3H is still on 12.23V, if yes you may need to replace SMC..

On this model fan will not spin untill processor is burning so dont worry about it....
